A former head of state, General Yakubu Gowon and former head of Interim National Government, Chief Ernest Shonekan are among the dignitaries at the Eagle Square in Abuja, venue of the today’s swearing-in ceremony. President Muhammadu Buhari and Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo are to be sworn-in for second term at the venue. Our correspondent reports that former presidents Olusegun Obasanjo and Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida are yet to arrive the venue. Other dignitaries include members of the diplomatic corps, business mogul, Aliko Dangote, governors, chieftains of the All Progressives Congress (APC), lawmakers, among others. Daily Trust reports that there was tight security at the venue.  Details later… May 29: Handover ceremony begin John Kerry, other world leaders arrive for Buhari's inauguration Jonathan decorates Osinbajo with GCON, dissolves cabinet Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin